						               													<description>An educational game aimed at school &amp;amp; college students. It is based upon manufacturing and trading in competition with other players, managing resources. Can be played by teams and has a number of levels of detail which can be adapted to suit the group. Comes complete with teachers notes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game consists of two games, the simpler &amp;quot;trader&amp;quot; version which, with additional rules and pieces, becomes the &amp;quot;manufacturer&amp;quot; version and it is this latter that is described below. Players may buy manufacturing machines (to make product), trucks (to deliver product) and representative cars (to get customers). They will need to pay manufacturing costs and operating costs and then deliver product to customers to earn money. Rep. cars are simply placed at a customer and remain there until product is delivered. Trucks move as dice throws, one die per truck, but all die are thrown together and player may select which die goes with which truck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object is to make the greatest profit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
